            . I am servant to Mr. John Michael, of <placeName id="t18310908-228-crimeloc1170">St. Albany's hotel, Charles-street, St. James'-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-228-crimeloc1170" type="placeName" value="St. Albany's hotel, Charles-street, St. James'-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-228-crimeloc1170" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-228-off1168 t18310908-228-crimeloc1170"></join>. On the evening of the 28th of August I placed a coat on a table in the house - it belonged to <rs id="t18310908-228-viclabel1171" type="occupation">Captain</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-228-victim1699 t18310908-228-viclabel1171"></join> James Laing, who was lodging in the house; I went down to clean the boots, and on returning I found the coat which the prisoner has on, laying on the stairs, but Captain 
               <persName id="t18310908-228-person1701">Laing</persName>
            's coat was gone; I had seen the prisoner standing in the tap-room when I went down; he came there again at half-past eight o'clock in the evening, with the captain's coat on.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I took it by mistake, instead of my own, and went back to rectify it. Witness. He did not tell me of it when he came back - he had no business to go into the room where the coat was; when I gave him into custody he said he had made a mistake - he walked into the tap-room, looked round, and was coming towards the door, as if to go out again, and I stopped him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-228-person1702">
                  THOMAS 
                  JOSEPH WEST
               <interp inst="t18310908-228-person1702" type="surname" value="JOSEPH WEST"></interp>
